</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(4/2/02 7:38:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Radical Ideas take 2</span><hr size=1> Disregarding what Tarek said (obviously a grammatical screwup), I think the list IS pretty radical, but has good ideas in it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some of my Favorites (Realistic could happen):<br>
<br>
- More pet-specific castings: not exactly the way you said it, but that general idea up the lvls is a good idea in my opinion.<br>
<br>
- a lesser mod rod:  I don't see why this isn't a good idea.  Enchanters got a lesser Clarity (breeze) with Kunark, so why not us a lesser mod rod?<br>
<br>
- stacked waterstones: I like this, but to be balanced, should be a multi-charge lore item.  Otherwise underwater/The Grey, would have no challenge whatsoever with enough prep time.  Maybie a multi-charged waterstone at a moderately high lvl, but below 50 (44 maybie).<br>
<br>
- the summoned items ideas: better bandages, and the <br>
other suggestions would be an interesting idea.  Limited real value to groups, but helps, and not unrealisitic, though unimportant IMO.<br>
<br>
- all 2HB to 1HB summons: I agree with this.  What caster type DOESN'T have a Stein of Moggok for almost their low to mid lvls ( i dunno about higher.  Not there yet, so i dunno).  To be truely useful, all of those staffs should be 1HB<br>
<br>
- ultra-taunt pet: I dunno.  I don't think exactly in this form, but maybie make our existing pets taunt better, since they aren't that great at it, and maybie make our earth root stick MOST of the time, rather then occasionally<br>
<br>
- about /pet hold: It should be a gained ability at a high lvl, NOT an AA ability.  For all pet classes.  Maybie somewhere in lvls 35 - 40.  Having it only on the ultra-high-end is unfair to most.  It shouldn't be that high.<br>
<br>
- What he probably meant is &quot;Pets indifferent to any mob that the mage didn't tell him/her to attack, or that is actively attacking the mage.  Only under those circumstances will the pet attack the mob.&quot;: I support this.  Pets shouldn't pull trains down on you.<br>
<br>
- Pet HP and Atk ratings: It probably needs increasing, but that is an intricate balance thing.  With increased DD by mages, and better pet taunt, may be unnecessary.  We'll see.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some of the ones I think are cool, but not realistic:<br>
<br>
- item to change fire/cold resists: I'd love this, but it throws off the whole advantage/disadvantage each class has fighting in some areas with different resist castings.  I can see why it'd be useful, but pretty unbalancing unless any class could get their own, but even then it would be a have/have not situation in the magician community.<br>
<br>
- elemental gates: we are not wizards.  We can't port. Get used to it.<br>
<br>
- almost everything else i didn't list here  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
<br>
I think its a very creative list, with some great ideas, but I just can't see most of it implemented.  Some of it IS good, but some just isn't, and looks like we mages want ALL of it.  It is good to get a complete (if somewhat nuts) list of all the ideas out there.  The magician community just needs to decide which ones we REALLY want.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp.  Flame away.  I'll respond (eventually).<br>
<br>
