<br>
I like all the discussion and refinement of the bandages thing.  And like Sscale said, we are the only casters that have BW skill anyways!<br>
<br>
I agree the pet taunt stuff might cause problems, but if pets are the main way we cause dmg, making a pure taunt pet still makes us a crappy wizard with a sometimes can taunt it off of us root spell.  It has to do dmg as well unless we are getting a MAJOR dmg increase, which I don't think is what we really want anyways.  I know its unlikely,  but pets should be able to keep the agro of a mob almost as well as a pure tank, or else they don't help a whole lot.<br>
<br>
An idea I saw on another thread here was for our pet buff and heal lines to be able to be casted on ANY pet.  I always kinda wondered why this was NOT already there?  What's the difference between a mage buffing/healing his own pet and him buffing somebody else's?  Especially the healing.  If 2 or 3 mages are together, usually only one pet is being agroed at a time, so all of them healing it is much better than just one.  Also mentioned in that thread would be to make all of the pet spells by other classes cross-class and cross-pet compatable.  I think this would be great as well.  Some limitations to it would obviously be necessary (a BST buffing up your lvl 4 elemental to lvl 40 would be somewhat extreme), but most spells should work to encourage pet-hunting parties.  Since most other classes don't like pets in their group, we should be allowed to hunt with each other!  To help facilitate this, I remember a dev stating that there is some kind of limit on the # of pets that can target a mob at once.  This would hurt us in this kind of situation.  We SHOULD be able to hunt together and not be limited by such a nerf.<br>
<br>
The last part of that was kind of a rant, but I think that it isn't unreasonable.  Read the &quot;Burnout as a Player Buff&quot; thread to see more ideas and debate along the last line.<br>
