Either inherently gained at level 51 (like ranger double archery damage) or archetype skill for pet classes. Has the effect of telling the pet to back off, and to stay backed off for 1-5 seconds depending on level or how many points you put in the AA.<br>
<br>
can scribe no drop copy of any spell out of your spellbook to use in chain research. only problem I see with this is all the spell turn-in quests.<br>
<br>
an &quot;escape&quot; pet, every spell level or every other spell level, starting early, that can't be used to keep the pet off you while you nuke. Most of the escape pet proposals I've seen are something like &quot;pet with tons of HP, insane taunt, and snare or root&quot;. Umm...if I had a pet like that, I wouldn't use anything else when solo. Solution: pet that has quite a few HP, very low damage output, high AC, low taunt, and casts the crappy level 14 bard AE mez song, which happens to be insane taunt. Maybe make it agro on whatever you have targetted when you summon it, and it dies when it loses all agro, and it doesn't listen to any commands.<br>
<br>
Summon for a stun item. Spell to summon it should be slow to cast, cost a decent amount of mana, and maybe have a long refresh time. Stun itself should be 1.0seconds or faster, very low resist. Item should be no drop/lore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ud5aidan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>D5 AidaN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/02 10:04:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: less radical ideas</span><hr size=1> I was in Air last Wednesday, luclin elemental models on....looked like a Genie gal to me =) <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34808>Aidonis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uimaginos9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Imaginos9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#333333>(4/8/02 8:50:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=154.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: less radical ideas</span><hr size=1> Ok so now we have conflicting info? Is the genie in air on or off?<br>
